00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.720
Selling Your Home When You Have Pets.

00:00:02.837 --> 00:00:06.917
Selling a home with pets is very common,
but may require extra preparation.

00:00:07.757 --> 00:00:10.597
Here are some tips we suggest
when selling a home with pets.

00:00:11.650 --> 00:00:15.340
For showings, removing pets from the
home is the most recommended option.

00:00:15.849 --> 00:00:20.110
This allows the buyer to walk through
the home without distractions and focus

00:00:20.110 --> 00:00:22.049
on how the space would feel for them.

00:00:23.280 --> 00:00:27.949
Even calm, well-behaved pets can be a
distraction, which may shorten a showing

00:00:28.199 --> 00:00:30.219
and take focus off the home itself.

00:00:30.762 --> 00:00:34.562
If removing pets isn’t possible,
then they need to be put in a crate.

00:00:34.852 --> 00:00:39.712
For the pet’s comfort and safety, using a
breathable cover over the crate can help

00:00:39.742 --> 00:00:43.912
reduce stress and discourage buyers from
approaching the crate during showings.

00:00:44.752 --> 00:00:49.852
Any crated pet must be placed in the
same location every time, exactly as

00:00:49.852 --> 00:00:51.652
noted in the listing instructions.

00:00:52.262 --> 00:00:55.422
This information is sent to
the agent prior to a showing

00:00:55.422 --> 00:00:57.262
so they know what to expect.

00:00:57.825 --> 00:01:00.354
Pets should never be
loose in the backyard.

00:01:00.854 --> 00:01:05.174
Buyers expect to walk the entire property,
including outdoor areas, and should be

00:01:05.174 --> 00:01:07.285
able to do that safely and comfortably.

00:01:08.450 --> 00:01:12.180
If you have pets in cages or tanks,
like birds, fish, reptiles, or

00:01:12.180 --> 00:01:15.870
small animals, make sure their
enclosures are clean and odor-free.

00:01:16.979 --> 00:01:19.569
Odors are one of the
biggest concerns for buyers.

00:01:20.430 --> 00:01:23.390
Professional carpet and furniture
cleaning is highly recommended,

00:01:23.779 --> 00:01:27.250
since pet smells often live in
furniture, not just flooring.

00:01:28.450 --> 00:01:31.769
Avoid heavy candles or air
fresheners, as buyers may think

00:01:31.769 --> 00:01:32.970
something is being covered up.

00:01:34.269 --> 00:01:38.269
If you’re unsure about odors, ask someone
outside the home for honest feedback.

00:01:38.850 --> 00:01:40.430
Finally, reduce pet clutter.

00:01:40.739 --> 00:01:43.839
Store toys, bowls, leashes,
and beds neatly so the home

00:01:43.839 --> 00:01:45.420
feels clean and clutter free.

00:01:46.112 --> 00:01:49.502
Preparing the home this way helps
keep the focus where it should

00:01:49.502 --> 00:01:51.322
be, on the property itself.

